race.comment: SUBARCTIC (2) tough stayer expected to play a leading role here out to his preferred trip. Went back from the outside gate and made ground late in the straight when ninth over 1500m at Newcastle. Winning rider hops back aboard and goes close. RHINESTONE LAD (5) deep into the prep now and kept finding when second over 2200m at Scone. Will roll forward again in a race devoid of speed. Top three player. SURREAL I AM (3) yet to win past 1650m and jumps out quickly in trip for this. Anchored with the 58.5kg when a plugging fourth last time out over 1600m at Newcastle nine days ago. No shock to see him play a leading role. SEETHING SEB (8) looks the pick of the rest third-up and has an okay record at this trip. Strong through the line when sixth over 1500m at Port Macquarie. Value contender.
